{
  "mcpServers": {
    "vault-search": {
      "command": "python",
      "args": [
        "/full/path/to/vault_mcp_server.py"
      ],
      "env": {}
    }
  }
}

IMPORTANT NOTES:

1. Replace "/full/path/to/vault_mcp_server.py" with the ACTUAL full path
   Examples:
   - Windows: "C:\\Users\\YourName\\vault-archive-product\\vault_mcp_server.py"
   - Mac: "/Users/yourname/vault-archive-product/vault_mcp_server.py"
   - Linux: "/home/yourname/vault-archive-product/vault_mcp_server.py"

2. Make sure search_daemon.py is RUNNING before starting Claude Desktop
   Start it with: python search_daemon.py

3. Your actual Claude Desktop config is located at:
   - Windows: %APPDATA%\Claude\claude_desktop_config.json
   - Mac: ~/Library/Application Support/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json
   - Linux: ~/.config/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json

4. Add the "vault-search" section to your existing config's "mcpServers" object
   Don't replace the entire file - just add this server to the list

5. Restart Claude Desktop COMPLETELY after adding this config
   (Quit the app entirely, then reopen)

Example of complete config file with multiple MCP servers:

{
  "mcpServers": {
    "filesystem": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "@modelcontextprotocol/server-filesystem", "C:\\allowed\\path"]
    },
    "vault-search": {
      "command": "python",
      "args": ["C:\\Users\\YourName\\vault-archive-product\\vault_mcp_server.py"]
    }
  }
}
